# Class label identify 
dict_wrist = {'Brush_teeth':0, 'Climb_stairs':1, 'Comb_hair':2, 'Descend_stairs':3, 'Drink_glass':4,
              'Eat_meat':5,'Eat_soup':6,'Getup_bed':7,'Liedown_bed':8,'Pour_water':9,'Sitdown_chair':10,
              'Standup_chair':11,'Use_telephone':12,'Walk':13 }

# Read file for al class
def read_file(dict_wrist):
    '''
        Hm c file 
        -----------------
        Tham s:
            class_dict: mt dictionary cha 14 hnh ng c gn nhn t 0 n 13
        -----------------
        Tr v: 
            X: mt list c len = 14 cha d liu  c c (Mi phn t ca list c dng numpy array cha cc sample ca nhn )
    '''
    X = []
    for c in dict_wrist.keys():
        f = glob.glob(root + c + '/*')
        d = read_each_file(f, cls=c)
        X.append(d)
    return X #type list

# Read file by class
def read_each_file(files, cls):
    temp = []
    for f in files:
        data = pd.read_table(f, sep=' ', header=None)
        data = np.array(data)
        temp.append(data)
    return temp

# Data processing: split features and their corresponding labels into proper format
def prepare_data(data):
    '''
        Hm tch features v labels
        ---------------------------
        Tham s: 
            data: list cha cc d liu va c c
         ---------------------------------------------
        idx| size | value                            |
        ----------------------------------------------
        0  |  12  | (2167,3), (844,3), ...           |
        ----------------------------------------------
        1  | 102  | (270,3) , (270,3), ...           |
        ----------------------------------------------
        2  |  31  | ...                              |
        ----------------------------------------------
        3  |  42  | ...                              |
        ----------------------------------------------
        .  | ...  |
        .  | ...  | ...                              |
        .  | ...  |
        ----------------------------------------------
        13 | 100  | (1170,3), (956,3)                |
        ----------------------------------------------
        Tr v:
            X: list c chiu di l 839, tng ng 839 samples
            y: 839 labels
    '''
    X = []
    y = []
    for i,f in enumerate(data):
        for ii in f:
            X.append(ii)
            y.append(i)
    return X, y

# Define padding function
def padding(X):
    '''
        Hm padding 
        --------------
        Tham s:

            X: mt list c chiu di 839, mi phn t l mt numpy array c dng (k,3)
        ----------------------
        idx |   size (k,3)   |
        ----------------------
        0   |  (2167,3)      |
        ----------------------
        1   |  (844,3)       |
        ----------------------
        2   |  (2228,3)      |
        ----------------------
        3   | ...            |
        ----------------------
        .   | ...            |
        .   | ...            |
        ----------------------
        838 |  (1050,3)      |
        ----------------------
        Tr v: 
            X: list c chiu di 839, mi phn t l mt nummpy array c dng (9318,3)

    '''
    #Tm gi tr k ln nht (kx3)
    max=0
    for i in X:
        if i.shape[0] > max:
            max = i.shape[0]

    # Padding
    for i in range(len(X)):
        if X[i].shape[0] < max:
            temp = X[i][X[i].shape[0]-1]
            temp = np.tile(temp, (max-X[i].shape[0], 1))
            X[i] = np.append(X[i],temp,axis= 0)
    return X

Implement Kmeans clustering step by step:

In [10]:
# Define euclidean distancce metric
def euclidean_dist(X,centroids):
    #Calculate euclidean_distance
    return distance.cdist(X, centroids, 'euclidean')

# Update new centroid in kmeans algorithm
def update_new_centroid(X,new_labels,K):
    #Update centroids
    return np.array([X[new_labels == k].mean(axis=0) for k in range(K)])

# check convergence function
def has_converge(centers, new_centers):
    # return True if two sets of centers are the same
    return (set([tuple(a) for a in centers]) == 
        set([tuple(a) for a in new_centers]))

# Define Kmeans clusturing algorithm
def Kmeans_Clustering(X,K):

    #Convert data to numpy array 
    if type(X) != np.ndarray:
        X = X.to_numpy()

    # randomly pick k rows of X as initial centers
    k_initial = np.random.choice(len(X), K ,replace = False)
    centroids = [X[k_initial,:]]
    label = []
    it = 0
    while 1:
        
        Dist = euclidean_dist(X,centroids[-1]) #Calculate euclidean_distance
        new_labels = np.argmin(Dist,axis=1)   #assign new labels
        label.append(new_labels)

        #Update centroids
        new_centroids = update_new_centroid(X,new_labels,K)
        #Check converge
        if has_converge(centroids[-1], new_centroids):
            break
        centroids.append(new_centroids)
        it += 1
    return label

S khc nhau gia cc metric:

  • accuracy_score:

    Trong bi ton phn loi a nhn, hm ny tnh ton chnh xc ca tp hp con: tp hp nhn c d on cho mt mu phi khp chnh xc vi tp nhn tng ng trong y_true.

  • rand_score:

    Ch s Rand tnh ton o tng t gia hai cm bng cch xem xt tt c cc cp mu v m cc cp c ch nh trong cc cm ging nhau hoc khc nhau trong cm c d on v ng.

    The raw RI score is:

    RI = (number of agreeing pairs) / (number of pairs)

  • silhouette_score:

    H s Silhouette c tnh bng cch s dng khong cch trung bnh trong cm ( a) v khong cch trung bnh trong cm gn nht ( b) cho mi mu.

    Gi tr tt nht l 1 v gi tr km nht l -1. Cc gi tr gn 0 cho bit cc cm chng cho. Cc gi tr m thng ch ra rng mt mu c ch nh sai cm, v mt cm khc ging nhau hn.

Nhn xt:

Qua Kmeans phn cm trn tp d liu padding v kim tra vi cc o khc nhau chng ta thy:

  • accuracy_score cho kt qu khng tt (0.084625) trn min accuracy [0,1]. iu ny cho thy c trng padding khng tt cho kha cnh phn lp.
  • rand_score biu din s khong cch gia cc cm. Khong cch cng xa th rand_score cng nh v khi rand_score nh th kt qu phn cm mi tt. Tuy nhin, vi c trng padding, rand_score li cho kt qu ngc li (0.852740), iu ny cho thy cc cm phn c bng c trng padding l gn nhau v khng tt cho qu trnh phn cm.
  • silhouette_score c min gi tr l [-1,1], biu din kh nng 1 im d liu c c phn cm ng hay khng. Vi c trng padding, kt qu thu c l (0.190629). tt vi kha cnh phn cm im d liu l mc trung bnh. -> Kt lun: kt qu tnh ton ca phn cm d liu qua phng php padding cho kt qu km 2 trn 3 o. iu ny cho thy c trng padding khng tt vi bi ton phn cm vi d liu dng chui(timeseries).

Dimensionality reduction using Autoencoder¶

In [72]:
class AE(nn.Module):
  def __init__(self, **kwargs):
    super(AE, self).__init__()
    self.input_shape, self.encoder_shape = kwargs['input_shape'], kwargs['encoder_shape']

    # Encoder
    self.encoder = nn.Sequential(
      nn.Linear(self.input_shape, self.encoder_shape),
      nn.ReLU()
    )

    # Decoder
    self.decoder = nn.Sequential(
      nn.Linear(self.encoder_shape, self.input_shape)
    )
        
  def forward(self, X):
    encoded=self.encoder(X)
    decoded=self.decoder(encoded)
    return decoded

def train(model, error, optimizer, n_epochs, x):
    model.train()
    for epoch in range(1, n_epochs + 1):
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        output = model(x)
        loss = error(output, x)
        loss.backward()
        optimizer.step()

        if epoch % int(0.1*n_epochs) == 0:
            print(f'epoch {epoch} \t Loss: {loss.item()}')

device = torch.device("cuda" if torch.cuda.is_available() else "cpu")

time_start = time.time()

model = AE(input_shape=wrist_X.shape[1], encoder_shape=5).double().to(device)
error = nn.MSELoss()
optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=1e-14, weight_decay=1e-3)

X_ae = torch.from_numpy(wrist_X).double().to(device)
train(model, error, optimizer, 1000, X_ae)

with torch.no_grad():
    encoded = model.encoder(X_ae)
    decoded = model.decoder(encoded)
    mse = error(decoded, X_ae).item()
    enc = encoded.cpu().detach().numpy()
    dec = decoded.cpu().detach().numpy()

time_ec = time.time() - time_start
print('Autoencoder done! Time elapsed: {} seconds'.format(time_ec))

Tng kt

  • c trng PCA, KPCA, ICA v Autoencoder cho kt qu tt hn padding baseline tt c cc o. iu ny cho thy c 4 phng php ni trn thnh cng trong vic rt trch cc c trng chnh ca ca d liu padding, gip lm gim thiu lng thng tin d tha - nhc im chnh ca padding.

  • c trng t-SNE cho kt qu tt hn so vi baseline vi 2 trn 3 o (tr o rand_score). iu ny cho thy c trng t-SNE cng thnh cng trong vic gi li thng tin ct li ca d liu padding, tuy nhin, li lm gim i tnh cht phn bit gia cc cm khi dng t-SNE vo Kmeans.

  • Vi u im l mt gii thut thun, PCA thnh cng trong vic ti u tc tnh ton. Ngoi ra, s chiu cn biu din cho c trng PCA l nh nht trong 5 phng php c c nn tc d on ca gii thut Kmeans cng c tng ln.

  • Kt qu ca KPCA km hn PCA trn 2 trong 3 o c cp, thi gian x l cng lu hn. iu ny cho thy d liu khng cha nhiu thng tin phi tuyn v vic dng KPCA a phn lm mt mt thng tin quan trng.

  • c trng ICA cng khng cho kt qu tt hn so vi PCA (d kt qu c cao hn so vi baseline). iu ny cho thy d liu khng cha nhiu thnh phn c lp v mt thng k.

  • c trng autoencoder cho kt qu mc trung bnh nhng li tiu tn rt nhiu thi gian hun luyn v rt trch c trng.

Kt lun chung: Vi kt qu vt tri trn c 3 o v thi gian x l nhanh. PCA l phng php gim s chiu mang li hiu qu v c tc ln cht lng cao nht khi c dng trn d liu padding.
